<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-11-11T20:03:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-11-11T20:03:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                        <head>283. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission to the United
                                Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                State</gloss><note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d283fn1">Source:
                                National Archives, RG 59, Central Files 1967–69, <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> 6 <gloss target="#t_CHIC1">CHICOM</gloss>. Limited Official Use; Priority. Repeated to
                                Taipei and Hong Kong.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1969-11-12T01:03:00+00:00">November 12, 1969,
                                0103Z</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4146. <gloss target="#t_CHIR1">Chirep</gloss> Vote Results.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss> voted Nov 11 on <gloss target="#t_CHIR1">Chirep</gloss> reses with following results: <list>
                                    <label>A.</label>
                                    <item>Important Question <gloss target="#t_RES1">res</gloss>
                                        adopted by vote of 71–48–4, 3 absent (73–47–5 in
                                        1968).</item>
                                    <label>B.</label>
                                    <item>Albanian <gloss target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> defeated
                                        48–56–21, 1 absent (44–58–23 in 1968). (This one vote less
                                        than margin forecast <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>
                                            3978.)<note n="2" xml:id="d283fn2">Dated Novembr 5.
                                            (Ibid.)</note>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Changes from 1968 were as follows: <list>
                                    <label>A.</label>
                                    <item>Important Question: Ecuador–Abstain to yes; Equatorial
                                        Guinea–Yes to absent; Kuwait–No to absent; Libya–yes to no;
                                        Malaysia–Yes to abstain; Morocco–No to abstain. Favorable
                                        margin thus decreased from 26 to 23.</item>
                                    <label>B.</label>
                                    <item>Albanian res: No to abstain: Belgium, Chile and Italy;
                                        Abstain to yes: Ghana, Libya, Mauritius and Nigeria. Only
                                        favorable change was Senegal from abstain to no. Favorable
                                        margin thus decreased from 14 to 8.</item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_YCW1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Yost</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>